<casebody firstpage="1021" lastpage="1021" xmlns="http://nrs.harvard.edu/urn-3:HLS.Libr.US_Case_Law.Schema.Case_Body:v1">
<parties id="p-1">
  In the Matter of Stanley M. CHESLEY.
 </parties>
<docketnumber id="p-2">
  No. D-2731.
 </docketnumber>
<court id="p-3">
  Supreme Court of the United States
 </court>
<decisiondate id="p-4">
  Nov. 18, 2013.
 </decisiondate>
<attorneys id="p-5">
  Stanley M. Chesley, of Cincinnati, Ohio, having requested to resign as a member of the Bar of this Court, it is ordered that his name be stricken from the roll of attorneys permitted to the practice of law before this Court. The Rule to Show Cause, issued on June 17, 2013, is discharged.
 </attorneys>
<opinion type="majority">
</opinion>
</casebody>
